-- Sanofi Said It Repurchased $233.8 Million of Shares This Month
-- B y   P h i l   S e r a f i n o
-- 2011-12-28T10:43:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-28/sanofi-said-it-repurchased-233-8-million-of-shares-this-month.html
Sanofi  has repurchased 178.9 million
euros ($233.8 million) of its shares this month, according to
filings on the French drugmaker’s  website .  Sanofi bought 1.88 million shares at an average price of
52.84 euros each from Dec. 7 to Dec. 9, 1.2 million shares at an
average of 53.54 euros each Dec. 14 to Dec. 16, and 285,000
shares at an average 53.68 euros each Dec. 19 to Dec. 20,
according to the undated filings. The stock rose 1.6 percent to
56.10 euros at 11:42 a.m. in Paris, where the company is based.  Sanofi said in September it would continue with
“opportunistic” buybacks.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Phil Serafino at 
 pserafino@bloomberg.net  